# Additional Resources: Podcasts, YouTube Channels, 
Newsletters & Blogs on AI-Powered SEO Content Production

This document covers key media resources beyond individual 
experts — channels, shows, and publications that 
consistently cover AI-powered SEO content production and 
are worth monitoring for ongoing research.

---

## YouTube Channels

**Ahrefs**
- URL: https://www.youtube.com/@AhrefsTV
- Why relevant: One of the most consistently high-quality 
  SEO education channels. Covers AI content workflows, 
  programmatic SEO, and content strategy with real data 
  and case studies. Not personality-driven — purely 
  tactical and tool-focused.

**Semrush**
- URL: https://www.youtube.com/@semrush
- Why relevant: Regular videos on AI SEO tools, content 
  production at scale, and B2B search strategy. Also 
  hosts interviews with practitioners including Nathan 
  Gotch and others on this expert list.

**Moz**
- URL: https://www.youtube.com/@Moz
- Why relevant: Long-running Whiteboard Friday series 
  covers SEO fundamentals and has increasingly focused 
  on AI's impact on search and content quality standards.

**Surfer SEO**
- URL: https://www.youtube.com/@SurferSEO
- Why relevant: Directly relevant — Surfer is one of the 
  leading AI-assisted content optimization tools. Their 
  channel covers AI content workflows, NLP-based writing, 
  and scaling SEO content production.

